A quick inspection of the code indicates what appears to be a non-sensical
condition:
  if (str == null && !str.equals("")) { ... }

See link, or snippet below:

public class P4Sync extends P4Base {
    ...
    public void setLabel(String label) throws BuildException {
        if (label == null && !label.equals("")) {
            throw new BuildException("P4Sync: Labels cannot be Null or Empty");
        }
    ...

Work around is to extend P4Sync, and put some guards in place.

I guess the intention was: 

   if (label == null || label.equals("")) 

which is what makes sense given the Build exception is trying to throw.
